HEADWORD: bondable
<hw>bondable</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>capable of being
fastened or secured with a rope or bond.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> bindable.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>capable of holding together or cohering; as
particles in a mass.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bondage</ent>⟦br⟧
